access: Apartment is located on the 2nd floor of a modern apartment building. You'll have access to the rooftop and gym. The apartment is my home and I hope you enjoy your stay.
additional_house_rules:
• Our home is your home during your stay, but please, just be respectful. No pets, no smoking, no breaking anything (!), no parties and/or large groups allowed.
• Treat our place with kindness and care as if it were your own. There are many small details that go into our place and we expect nothing to go home with you. 
• Rooftop rules: No BBQs, No parties, No open fire, No glass bottles, No loud music. Remember your key to get access onto the roof!
• Sliding Door rules: Do not leave this open when you are not in the apartment. Please keep the door locked and the safety board in place when not in use. 
• If anyone in the building asks, you are friends of ours staying with us. No need to mention the words "AirBnB" :) Thanks friends!
description:
You’ll love my place because of the high ceilings, open kitchen, and the location. You're two blocks away from Bedford and in between the L and the JMZ subway stops. You'll have access to the spacious rooftop with views of Manhattan, perfect for a glass of wine in the evening.

The space is two stories so the apartment has extremely high ceilings, an open kitchen, and a large living area. It has sliding glass doors that open to a juliet balcony to let fresh air and light in. Even better, you're in the heart of Williamsburg and only one stop from Manhattan.

Apartment is located on the 2nd floor of a modern apartment building. You'll have access to the rooftop and gym. The apartment is my home and I hope you enjoy your stay.

As little or as much as needed. I use Airbnb regularly when I travel and am willing to adapt to what you need.

Williamsburg is an active and eclectic neighborhood in Brooklyn. You get the best of restaurants, nightlife, shopping, and views of the Manhattan skyline (from the water front). You are one stop from Manhattan on the L train, which makes it easy to enjoy all that NYC has to offer!

SUBWAY: The L Train is located at N 7th and Driggs. Exit the building and take a left. The first cross street is Driggs. Head North (take a right) and walk for about 10 min. You’ll see the subway entrance. You can buy a metrocard there. Manhattan is one stop away .

UBER: Uber is an easy way to get around. If you aren’t already an Uber user, download the app in the app store, and you can effortlessly contact a driver to take you to your desired location

TAXI: Taxis are not always frequent, but if you’d like to hail one and have time, I recommend walking to the corner of Driggs and S. 2nd St to hail one.

hosts.about:
Eater. Drinker. Traveler. Dreamer…

I like to explore a destination from a local's point of view, so any suggestions relative to the best neighborhoods, restaurants, boutiques, parks and museums/galleries are much appreciated.

I'm a very mellow guest, as most of my energy is spent outside of the home, absorbing the local culture and community. However, I always welcome a friendly conversation and love to talk travel.

Looking forward to meeting you!

I have been on the go since the day I was born and have lived in 12 different cities so far (Frankfurt, Austin,  Seattle, and New York are highlights). 
One could argue that I was raised to travel, and thankfully I love exploring new places (both foreign and domestic). When I'm not traveling, I work in Marketing for a tech company. I am active (I love running, cycling, yoga, etc) and enjoy the arts (visual arts are my favorite). I am
an avid reader and really love maps. I have an insatiable desire to learn and am always looking for insider tips on the places I visit.
